commit_message:
Skip some tests when cinder is not enabled

test_delete_server_while_in_attached_volume:
    Skip when cinder is not enabled.
ServerRescueTestJSON:
    No test access the volume resource_setup creates, so stop creating one.
ServerRescueNegativeTestJSON:
    Move volume creation into tests that use it and skip them when cinder
    is not enabled.

Change-Id: I8587c3e5ff3dbf5f23d09a5fd49b2c55c2ef7657

commit_message:
Activate pep8 check that _ is imported

Remove the specification in tox.ini that _ is a builtin so that
it will no longer assume that _ does not need to be imported.

This helps ensure that the _ from i18n is used.

Activating this check did not flag any violations.

Change-Id: I1dd9fed18051cac2d5d14b60eb94a03a4d35909a

Implements the VPN specific changes required for the service base
and insertion spec @ I595d7fe224f49f8cbc4203569d7862deaa74e1e7

the definition of ServiceBase and the ServiceInterface db models

commit_message:
Add ovs validation during agent boot up

There is no check during agent boot up, and setup operations
cause agent crash, as bug #1351135 confirmed. Add validation
check upon ovs, to prevent the crash.

Closes-bug: #1351135
Change-Id: Ifd0174b8324c3267ae6df971d51bfdc51523441d

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-08-21 22:29:47.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/linux/ip_lib.py'], 'message': 'Remove potential extra work in IpRouteCommand

Variable device_list initialisation and usage is messed up in method
IpRouteCommand.pullup_route. This lead to multiple remove/add same
routes on interface. It's not affect final result, but it does extra
work.

By the way, is someone know this method need for? Method's docsting tell
us "Ensures that the route entry for the interface is before all others
on the same subnet." But this have no sense.

Records in routing table sorted according to destination netmask.  More
specific rules goes first. more common goes last. If someone really need
to change order of records in routing table he should use separate
routing table (See "man ip-route" for info about routing tables and
routing rules. Don't mess routing rules and routing records.)

Change-Id: I0b4d937cbb30fe0f8e6a5f130943965447a551ab
'}]
commit_message:
Remove potential extra work in IpRouteCommand

Variable device_list initialisation and usage is messed up in method
IpRouteCommand.pullup_route. This lead to multiple remove/add same
routes on interface. It's not affect final result, but it does extra
work.

By the way, is someone know this method need for? Method's docsting tell
us "Ensures that the route entry for the interface is before all others
on the same subnet." But this have no sense.

Records in routing table sorted according to destination netmask.  More
specific rules goes first. more common goes last. If someone really need
to change order of records in routing table he should use separate
routing table (See "man ip-route" for info about routing tables and
routing rules. Don't mess routing rules and routing records.)

Change-Id: I0b4d937cbb30fe0f8e6a5f130943965447a551ab

commit_message:
lb-agent: refactor and fix bridge deletion

- Change delete_bridge function name to reflect that it doesn't only
  work with vlans but also for example with vxlan, same with
  delete_interface function.
- Make sure that linuxbridge agent doesn't delete vlan interfaces
  if they are specified in the physical_interface_mappings, fixing bug
  #1334634.

Change-Id: I182a1142b65435bb509c62f1c17db683ae5a7457
Closes-Bug: #1334634

commit_message:
ovs agent: port may lose vlan tag

When a port is added and then removed in short time, it may lose its
vlan tag permanently util be removed and added again.

Change-Id: Id3a3dc857dffb729b2bc3bfc96c30d313a690037
Closes-bug: 1328128

commit_message:
Ensure host_routes order in subnet

As route may be recursive, some routes must be installed after the
depending route. So we need a mechanism to set the order of host_routes
in subnet manually.

This patch add an order column to host_routes table, which describe the
order of routes, routes are applied from lower order to higher.

Gerrit Spec: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/94563/
Implements: blueprint neutron-route-order
Change-Id: I3d883db64cce1f145ceb997f2e42582475ebc86f
Closes-Bug: #1288606

instead.

commit_message:
Update router status of l3agent

Router status of l3agent has only ACTIVE.
But router should have other status such as PENDING_UPDATE and ERROR.

When ERROR occurs in l3agent process, neutron set "ERROR" to router status of DB.
This code is modified for l3agent(non DVR).

Change-Id: I44f03ea66d8e5ddb974963ecfa994b6af75c72c8

commit_message:
WIP:  Don't run ra_dvd inside of snat namespaces

This is a placeholder patch for now.  I need to work out where ra_dvd
should be run.  My initial feeling is that it should only be run in
qrouter namespaces and not snat namespaces.

BTW, a unit test failure in Jenkins is expected as long as this is a
WIP.

Change-Id: I8686bd7e672f986f6249f483e841825ecff15db6
Closes-bug: #WIP

commit_message:
Fix support of external gw-ip outside subnet

Before fix when l3-agent was trying to create a route with the
gateway IP which is outside the external network subnet, the
command was failing since the router namespace does not know anything
about the gateway IP/cidr.

After fix, a static route of gateway-ip is created before adding the
default route. Because of which now the gw-ip is known to router
namespace. Respective unit test cases also fixed.

Change-Id: Ie00c579710a81b19c2a27fc558b70a415ba16ae9
Closes-Bug: #1335023

commit_message:
OVS-Agent crashes when OVS dead(Alternative I)

Alternative patch of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/113450/
(Just for reference, and this line will be removed before merge.)
OVS crash/restart is unpredictable, so neutron-ovs-agent should be
robust enough under that situation. But currently ovs-agent doesn't
figure out this error status(only check ovs restarted status) and
still continue to apply subsequent opreations(set br/add patch
port/...) till causing exceptions/crash. Add proper fail-over code
to treat ovs dead/restart graceful, to prevent agent crash while it
is running. And handle ovs-dead error during ovs-agent boot up.

Closes-bug: #1296202
Change-Id: Ia8ecfbe5f95f6eed32e1b58bd7742f0b539fc506

commit_message:
db migration failed when plugin name alias used in config file

due to blueprint config-plugin-by-name[1], convenient plugin name alias
can be use in config file, but the db migration doesn't understand the
name alias. If the alias is used, when db migration try to get the name
of enabled core/service plugins, it will get the alias instead of full
the class name. The patch helps the db migration to resolve the alias
to the full class name.

[1] https://blueprints.launchpad.net/neutron/+spec/config-plugin-by-name

Closes-Bug: #1286052
Change-Id: Idf13417c85bfafa666ca1d9fb5e94a5164d74abd

commit_message:
Autocreated ports count against port quota

This commit adds a filter when counting port quota to avoid counting
auto-created ports used by neutron routers, dhcp servers and floating ip
addresses.

commit_message:
Added parsing format for ethernet alias names

Network-to-interface mapping format uses ':' to separate network from
interface. This syntax does not allow use of ethernet alias names.
Adding additional '|' separator which takes precedence over ':'.

Change-Id: I3d8f709d30d2bf7fc8b6375265972c9905889c5e
Closes-Bug: #1288641

commit_message:
Modular L2 Agent code fragments

Please note these code fragments are just for reviewing
possible approaches for building modular L2 agents. The
code submitted here is NOT functional. It is NOT a Poc
either. These code fragments are being put here for sharing
ideas and discussion in the ML2 subgroup.

Please review and comment in that spirit. All suggestions
for bettring this approach and/or for putting forward new
approaches are most welcome.

More info can be found in the following evolving etherpad:
https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/modular-l2-agent-outline

Change-Id: I71ab95709557df8ec477177ef8d88df71f93262d

revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-06-18 07:48:46.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/common/constants.py', 'neutron/common/utils.py', 'neutron/plugins/ml2/plugin.py'], 'message': 'ML2: Prevent lock wait timeout in update_port

The update_port routine performs a SELECT...FOR UPDATE query
on ports. However, if the same port is being deleted
concurrently, it might end up trying to acquire a lock which
will never be released if the thread performing delete_port
yielded from within the transaction.

This has been observed in upstream gating jobs, especially
in connection with update_port operations executed by the
load balancing service plugin.

This patch changes update_port by acquiring a semaphore
for database access before starting the transaction.
In order to avoid unnecessary global locks for db resources,
this patch changes lock name generation in way that
the lock applies only to the resource being update.
The lock name change is applied also to the other places
where the DB access lock is acquired.

commit_message:
ML2: Prevent lock wait timeout in update_port

The update_port routine performs a SELECT...FOR UPDATE query
on ports. However, if the same port is being deleted
concurrently, it might end up trying to acquire a lock which
will never be released if the thread performing delete_port
yielded from within the transaction.

This has been observed in upstream gating jobs, especially
in connection with update_port operations executed by the
load balancing service plugin.

This patch changes update_port by acquiring a semaphore
for database access before starting the transaction.
In order to avoid unnecessary global locks for db resources,
this patch changes lock name generation in way that
the lock applies only to the resource being update.
The lock name change is applied also to the other places
where the DB access lock is acquired.

Closes-Bug: 1313794

Change-Id: I9013942220dfd72358ca464459581ef0ad95e7c1

the commit message for a proposed spec if it proposes
changes to the Glance REST API. This will make it
much easier for people such as the API WG who want to
review API changes across OpenStack to find and
review proposed API changes.

commit_message:
Add read only API for default quotas

This patch add api function to get default quotas when request is like:
GET /v2.0/quotas/default ("default" is a special tenant-id to represent the
default quotas.)
It is variant (1) from comment
https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1204956/comments/1 in bug report

Change-Id: I26aa500d5dec632a9afd940402f1c0278ff981e0
Closes-Bug: 1204956

commit_message:
Ensure .egg-info metadata directory existed

Without .egg-info metadata directory, testcase which invokes entry points to
load plugins will fail.
This patch add "python setup.py egg_info" in run_test.sh to fix this.

Change-Id: I6eff4a8805e554f9a58e5395f0c6b607d7d2cbf8
Closes-Bug: 1204456

L3_agent router can't update external_gateway_info

We can change router external_gateway_info(external_network)
by RestAPI, but l3_agent can't update router external_network.

commit_message:
L2 pop removes unuseful regular mac learning rules

This patch removes the regular mac learning rules
when the l2 population mechanism driver is used.

Without the regular mac learning there is no more use of
the table 10 and the unknown unicasts will be droppped.
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Ovs-flow-logic

Closes-bug: #1297782
Change-Id: I1a47d493e00159d49c157a940927ab53edb799a2

commit_message:
Add cookie support to ovs_lib, ovs_neutron_agent

All of the flows on the integration bridge belonging to a vif's
OpenFlow port are removed on port_bound. Since the firewall is invoked
to setup port filters before connectivity is established (i.e. before
port_bound is called) this defeats an OVS-based firewall. To solve
this issue, a distinct cookie on flows that belong to the firewall
and a separate, distinct cookie on flows that belong to the agent
will be used. This will require OVS version 1.5.0+ to delete flows
based on a cookie.

DocImpact: Adds configuration parameter to ovs_neutron_plugin.ini

Change-Id: Ia9b3aa6a383c3465f595725442eca2db05f24a16
Partially-implements: blueprint ovs-firewall-driver

commit_message:
Assign local VLANs before port filters

Assign local VLANs ahead of establishing port filters so that
actions for OVS flows for security group rules can be appropriately
determined.

Provisioning cannot occur before security group port filters are in
place (connectivity would be established without security!). Also,
assignment must occur before security group port filters are in place
(firewall has to use the local vlan to forward the packet). Thus, the
correct order is to assign, secure, and then provision.

Change-Id: I18f585afc4a342ce97033021a3c3dfb1776695ba
Partially-implements: blueprint ovs-firewall-driver

commit_message:
Move yaql to stackforge

yaql is a library used by at least two Stackforge projects:
Mistral and Murano. Some other OpenStack projects evaluate yaql
for their own needs. Thus it will be beneficial to host yaql on
Stackforge.

Link to github repo:
https://github.com/ativelkov/yaql

Currently project is using standard OpenStack tools such as:
tox, pbr, hacking, testtools, etc

As a first step only docs, pep8 and py27 jobs will run in check
and gate queues. The plan is to run all the python-jobs, publish
docs to rtfd and publish releases to pypi via OpenStack Infra.

Change-Id: I2518fd98078f5e9fae79bbff353d2c184484c8f3

commit_message:
Enforce uniqueness of security group name per tenant

In Bug: 1194579 a race condition is described where multiple
requests to create 'default' security group may not be caught
as checks are in code, not enforced on the db model.

This review enforces the uniqueness of {tenant_id, sg_name}
in the SecurityGroup db model using a named UniqueConstraint.
I have included the migration file - please let me know if this
is correct. I don't think we need a test here as this case is
actually already covered in test_extension_security_group

Closes-Bug: 1194579

Change-Id: I9559aeed64942b828ec57611daa780ee6ef5bcb1

commit_message:
maint:Don't translate debug level logs

Our translation policy
(https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LoggingStandards#Log_Translation) calls
for not translating debug level logs. This helps to prioritize log
translation.
There were some commits that fixed it but ignored the the style like
msg = _('this is debug info'); LOG.debug(msg)
This commit fixes this style of LOG.debug.

Change-Id: I2cc3fe563456ba0906f74262ab1ba6967301d6d1

subject: Fix KeyError in dhcp_rpc when plugin.port_update raise exception
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 979, 'name': 'Dave Walker', 'email': 'email@daviey.com', 'username': 'davewalker'}, {'_account_id': 1420, 'name': 'Adam Gandelman', 'email': 'adamg@ubuntu.com', 'username': 'gandelman-a'}, {'_account_id': 5170, 'name': 'Microsoft Hyper-V CI', 'email': 'hyper-v_ci@microsoft.com', 'username': 'hyper-v-ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 9093, 'name': 'Chuck Carlino', 'email': 'chuckjcarlino@gmail.com', 'username': 'ChuckC'}, {'_account_id': 9656, 'name': 'Ihar Hrachyshka', 'email': 'ihrachys@redhat.com', 'username': 'ihrachys', 'status': 'Red Hat Networking Systems Engineer'}, {'_account_id': 9681, 'name': 'Ryu CI', 'email': 'ryu-openstack-review@lists.sourceforge.net', 'username': 'neutronryu', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 9682, 'name': 'OpenContrail CI', 'username': 'contrail', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 9732, 'name': 'Mellanox CI', 'email': 'mlnx-openstack-ci@dev.mellanox.co.il', 'username': 'mellanox', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 9787, 'name': 'Big Switch CI', 'email': 'openstack-ci@bigswitch.com', 'username': 'bsn', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 10119, 'name': 'vArmour CI', 'email': 'openstack-ci-test@varmour.com', 'username': 'varmourci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 10153, 'name': 'One Convergence CI', 'email': 'oc-neutron-test@oneconvergence.com', 'username': 'oneconvergence', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 10237, 'name': 'Numan Siddique', 'email': 'nusiddiq@redhat.com', 'username': 'numansiddique'}, {'_account_id': 10503, 'name': 'Huawei ML2 CI', 'email': 'huawei-openstack-ci@huawei.com', 'username': 'huawei-ci', 'inactive': True, 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 12040, 'name': 'A10 Networks CI', 'email': 'a10-openstack-ci@a10networks.com', 'username': 'a10networks-ci', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-11-12 12:43:02.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/api/rpc/handlers/dhcp_rpc.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/test_dhcp_rpc.py'], 'message': "Fix KeyError in dhcp_rpc when plugin.port_update raise exception

KeyError exception is seen because of following reasons

* DhcpRpcCallback._port_action() is called by two functions
   -  DhcpRpcCallback.create_dchp_port()
   -  DhcpRpcCallback.update_dhcp_port()

* When create_dhcp_port() function calls _port_action(), the
  function argument 'port' will have the body as
  {'port': {'network_id': foo_network_id, 'fixed_ips': [..] ...}

* When update_dhcp_port() function calls _port_action(), the
  function argument 'port' will have the body as
  {'id': port_id, 'port': {{'port': {'network_id': foo_network_id,
			            'fixed_ips': [..] ...}}

* If an exception occurs when _port_action() calls plugin.create_port(),
  network id is accessed as
  net_id = port['port']['network_id']

* If an exception occurs when _port_action() calls plugin.update_port(),
  network id is accessed as
  net_id = port['port']['network_id']
  which is causing the KeyError. network_id should have been accessed as
  net_id = port['port']['port']['network_id']

This patch fixes the issue by making the _port_action() take the
same port body. update_dhcp_port() insteading of passing the port_id
and port information in a single argument, it now adds port_id
in the port body itself.

commit_message:
Fix KeyError in dhcp_rpc when plugin.port_update raise exception

KeyError exception is seen because of following reasons

* DhcpRpcCallback._port_action() is called by two functions
   -  DhcpRpcCallback.create_dchp_port()
   -  DhcpRpcCallback.update_dhcp_port()

* When create_dhcp_port() function calls _port_action(), the
  function argument 'port' will have the body as
  {'port': {'network_id': foo_network_id, 'fixed_ips': [..] ...}

* When update_dhcp_port() function calls _port_action(), the
  function argument 'port' will have the body as
  {'id': port_id, 'port': {{'port': {'network_id': foo_network_id,
			            'fixed_ips': [..] ...}}

* If an exception occurs when _port_action() calls plugin.create_port(),
  network id is accessed as
  net_id = port['port']['network_id']

* If an exception occurs when _port_action() calls plugin.update_port(),
  network id is accessed as
  net_id = port['port']['network_id']
  which is causing the KeyError. network_id should have been accessed as
  net_id = port['port']['port']['network_id']

This patch fixes the issue by making the _port_action() take the
same port body. update_dhcp_port() insteading of passing the port_id
and port information in a single argument, it now adds port_id
in the port body itself.

Change-Id: I70b92fa20b421b05ca2053a9a57f62db726f7625
Closes-bug: #1378508
(cherry picked from commit 7ea605df3ac71dc568194bcd5eaf1c115008e1ee)

commit_message:
Translate 'powervm' hypervisor_type to 'phyp' for scheduling

This adds a temporary translation of the 'powervm' hypervisor type
image metadata to 'phyp' for scheduling.

The powervc-driver in stackforge uses the hypervisor type of 'powervm'
for scheduling so this is needed to make that work until the driver
can get a translation shim in place to convert powervm to phyp in
image metadata.

Closes-Bug: #1370613

Change-Id: I4b20ffcb9911806db821f2902e09248dfa89d845
(cherry picked from commit d05567cc3fcb8849402f7036895ea5f40f7e1a1f)

commit_message:
Fix L3 HA network creation to allow user to create router

Update HA Network creation to use an admin context to allow Neutron
to create the tenant-less network required for the HA router when
it does not yet exist and is being created by a non-admin user.

Neutron creates these resources without a tenant so users cannot see
or modify the HA network, ports, etc.  Port creation and association
already use elivated admin contexts to allow their function when
an user attempts to create a HA L3 router.

Conflicts:
        neutron/tests/unit/db/test_l3_ha_db.py

Change-Id: I36166158a0970b8d08d6702054b11a43fb684281
Closes-Bug: #1388716
(cherry picked from commit cc9bc24229f1d79dc99303db1affc03c030c011e)

commit_message:
Add in-instance docker software config hook

This hook uses 'docker-py' library to deploy containers
for a container-manifest embeded in software-config 'config'
property.

Container manifest uses standard google container manifest schema[1].

WARNING: This is an experimental implementation.

[1]https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/containers/container_vms.

Change-Id: I5ca30e99be1a247daf89c46aaa5a5034f1991379
Closes-Bug: #1380886

commit_message:
Change the periodic tempest "all" job to use neutron

The slow heat job is failing on the nightly tempest 'all' run in the
CfnInitScenarioTest.test_server_cfn_init test, but passes in the
slow heat job. The main differences seem to be that the nightly job runs a lot
more stuff (more stress), and the nightly job uses nova-network but the slow
heat job uses neutron. Changing the 'all' job to neutron will help debug
this and at this point we should be using neutron anyway.

Change-Id: I74afab102c1dcf52aef15b0f4f4f15bbfc08250a

commit_message:
Refactor generic cleanup mechanism part 2

Current cleanup mechanism is awful. It's hardcoded, without repeat on failures,
contains a lot of mistakes, in some places it is too fast (in case of deletion of VMs)
in other to slow (like deletion of users). As well there is mix of cleanup mechanism
and resource cleanup mechanism.
To resolve these all issues this patch introcude a cleanup engine that resolves all issues
above.
It's resource based, so to add new resouce you should just a make subclass of base.Resource
and probably override some of methods like (list, delete, is_deleted) and that's all.
All complexity of managing:
0) waiting until async deletion is finished
1) repeat on failure logic
2) greaceful failure handling
3) parallelization
4) plugin support
Is hidden deep inside cleanup engine
+ bonus we are able to specify now single resource (without clenaping whole service)

PART 2:
-------

* Write cleanup plugins for all tracked resources (on currnet moment)
* Switch cleanap context to use cleanup engine isntead of ald cleanup.utils
* Merge admin and user cleanup context (cause they are quite short now)
* Change quotas scenairos cleanup context configuration
* Fix resource names that are created by ceilometer scenarios

bp benchmark-context-cleanup-refactor

Change-Id: I85ab881fd65da4bb8263b4f72b9f751673ae5099

commit_message:
Run puppet unit tests on newer 3.x series versions

Puppet has advanced beyond 3.4. This adds tests to be run
in 3.6 and 3.7. 3.7 will be the last 3.x release. We don't need
to test 3.5 because it only existed for 2 weeks and was replaced
quickly by 3.6 because of some terrible bugs. Verion 3.3 is the
oldest puppet we will test against.

Discussion here http://tinyurl.com/ocsz4hj

Change-Id: I59d55f2a7e796087fb614788b76f62d09a13f729

commit_message:
Break V2 XML Support

DO NOT MERGE: First patch to see if this breaks XML support in a clean
way.

Nova's XML support has been deprecated with a warning that it could be
removed as early as Juno. Now that we are in Kilo we are ready to remove
support.  Before actually doing the surgery to properly remove XML
support, intentionally break XML support in a 'clean' way, so if someone
freaks out that we are removing XML support we can easily re-enable it.

Follow up to I4acc15ce5f487738bb34a95c2261a5d05d827d8d

Change-Id: I345ce62ab0cd6fde07338831b5675a23c94478c7

commit_message:
Let image upload happen after configuration is applied

In order to succesfully upload an image, it is important that the server side
got a chance to react to possibly updated configuration. The Glance_image class
itself also parses the configuration of the API service for stuff such as region
name. When any of these options are changed through the Glance_api_config, this
modification has to be saved on disk at the time the Glance_image class parses
the configuration file.

This patch utilizes the transitivity of the ~> operator where a change to a
Glance_api_config already notifies the Service['glance-api'].

Change-Id: I21d7c40de79b5e40421f9d645236ee972bd061e5

commit_message:
Set nginx default settings for master node

- increase number of workers from 2 to half available CPUs.
- enable epoll by default
- enable tcpnopush
- enable tcpnodelay
- disable server_token

These settings allow to bootstrap many nodes in parallel allowing
anaconda and debian installer to get all files without timeout.

Partial-Bug: 1384510
Partial-Bug: 1349360

Change-Id: I44054cf2afa1fa5a70ba064f4957b964947b2b2c
Implements: blueprint 100-nodes-support
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:

commit_message:
Add service_identity to openstacklib

The openstacklib::service_validation resource is a library resource that can
be used by nova, cinder, ceilometer, etc., rather than replicating equivalent
functionality across all of these modules to manage Keystone resources
like user, tenant, service, and endpoints.

Change-Id: Ice459f1048d6aa6d408f62517f13a83356f815f9
Implements: blueprint common-openstack-identity-resource

commit_message:
Allow to use custom mirror

The current configure_mirror.sh expects no-one
want to use other than openstack.org pypi mirrors.

Having the configure_mirror.sh to use a costum,
NODEPOOL_PYPI_MIRROR instead of NODEPOOL_REGION when defined.

It allows averyone to use his local pypi mirror, with his
nodepool.

Change-Id: I6f0bd3372be09ccf423caacff83e615038c96ec5

commit_message:
Add new Distil project

Distil is a rating service of OpenStack to provide easy
interactions with user's existing billing systems, by
exposing a configurable set of collection tools and
transformers to make usable rating data out of Ceilometer
entries.

commit_message:
Check stunnel.connect_host not stunnel.connect_ip

The various service configurations all check for
stunnel.connect_ip as part of the configuration for
enabling stunnel. This variable doesn't exist in any
template. However stunnel.connect_host exists in
ssl_source.yaml

Change-Id: Iee4dd33d5afde211f669346005c36f88c9ebeae2
Depends-On: I25c4bb09cf28a3728e959d4dd583af26a602ad90
Closes-Bug: #1391926

commit_message:
Add cinder v2 endpoints

As community nova(for Kilo) have switches to use cinder v2 api,
from cookbook perspective, it should be able to have Cinder v2 endpoint
supported.
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/124468/

It's suggested to have both Cinder api endpoints defined/register in place.
This will give benefit for release compatibility and also give flexibility
for end users that still want to adopt v1 api.

Change-Id: If6d6b39a75e23c5c46ff008bd24e11f42afa20f8

subject: Register Cinder v2 service and endpoint
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-13 11:58:54.000000000', 'files': ['recipes/identity_registration.rb'], 'message': 'Register Cinder v2 service and endpoint

Recently nova merged commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/124468/
have switch to use cinder v2.

The reason for cookbook bug 1388741 is that
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/132439/ miss a change for the cinder
service_name cinderv2. In simple, to make cinder command line to support
v2 api, it requires:

service_type=volumev2
service_name=cinderv2
endpoint url=http://<ip>:8776/v2/%(tenant_id)s

This commit will rely on the common cookbook change:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/134150/

Change-Id: Id447f22ad363c809c5678fbceb6c42c900086aa2
'}]
commit_message:
Register Cinder v2 service and endpoint

Recently nova merged commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/124468/
have switch to use cinder v2.

The reason for cookbook bug 1388741 is that
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/132439/ miss a change for the cinder
service_name cinderv2. In simple, to make cinder command line to support
v2 api, it requires:

service_type=volumev2
service_name=cinderv2
endpoint url=http://<ip>:8776/v2/%(tenant_id)s

This commit will rely on the common cookbook change:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/134150/

Change-Id: Id447f22ad363c809c5678fbceb6c42c900086aa2

cleanup files that are created for swift functional tests

Currently this portion of code is also being run when running
tox to debug local tests. Which is very annoying since a developer
will end up with a bunch of uuid files. Rather than creating it
once per run, we can have a setup/teardown that is handled safely.

commit_message:
Source lib/nova when upgrading tempest

In lib/nova is set variable NOVA_BIN_DIR which is later used for setting
cli_dir in tempest.conf. Without including lib/nova the variable is
evaluated as empty string.

Change-Id: I74f0cf8a3af287b072acefab92ac9a3facb443f5
Closes-Bug: 1391436
(cherry picked from commit d69386a2b78c53c48f734c48be15c217f9208981)

commit_message:
Fixes volume client in volume tests

volumes_client is coming from cls.os and volume_client is coming
from cls.os_adm. Here it creates a naming disaster for the volume
client. Adding admin_volume_client at the place of volume_client
fixes the client for admin user.

Change-Id: I0c55d3f7fbf4a096c012ffee3697f14869fe9962

commit_message:
Fix domain federation tokens for inherited roles.

Currently domain-scoped federation-generated tokens incorrectly
include group roles that are inherited to projects within that domain.
This error is also exposed via the /auth/domains and
/OS-FEDERATION/domains API calls. This patch fixes this.

Change-Id: I2b5c1e3d695dd7b27bf3b15361fccb5c13bdd554
Closes-bug: 1385533
Closes-bug: 1385643

Add limits to V3 and improve limits formatting in shell

Adds support for the limits API to the v3 client.

Also improve the formatting of absolute-limits from

+-------------------------+-------+
| Name                    | Value |
+-------------------------+-------+
| maxServerMeta           | 128   |
| maxPersonality          | 5     |
| maxImageMeta            | 128   |
| maxPersonalitySize      | 10240 |
| maxTotalRAMSize         | 51200 |
| maxSecurityGroupRules   | 20    |
| maxTotalKeypairs        | 100   |
| totalRAMUsed            | 512   |
| maxSecurityGroups       | 10    |
| totalFloatingIpsUsed    | 0     |
| totalInstancesUsed      | 1     |
| totalSecurityGroupsUsed | 1     |
| maxTotalFloatingIps     | 10    |
| maxTotalInstances       | 2     |
| totalCoresUsed          | 1     |
| maxTotalCores           | 20    |
+-------------------------+-------+

to

+--------------------+------+-------+
| Name               | Used | Max   |

| ImageMeta          | -    | 128   |
| Instances          | 1    | 2     |

commit_message:
Provide a single stunnel connect_host

At present connect_host is specified by each port, individually, as
the same value. Move connect_host to be a direct child of the stunnel
element so it is only specified once.

Although previously we could theoretically specify a different
connect_host for each service, in practice they were the same and
that never would have worked.

This change means Mustache like {{#stunnel.connect_host}} will work.

Change-Id: I25c4bb09cf28a3728e959d4dd583af26a602ad90
Partial-Bug: #1391926

commit_message:
Upgrade to avoid vulnerable requests-kerberos versions

All versions of requests-kerberos prior to 0.6 do not properly handle
mutual authentication. In short this means that the server was never
properly verified and a client could potentially send sensitive data to
an untrusted server.

Conflicts:
	global-requirements.txt

Change-Id: I1e9a3b1af15e69ae5c155a146638774cf472ef33
(cherry picked from commit 37404dc3ae56ab021da220b38242bba6fc44c47d)

commit_message:
Refactor generic cleanup mechanism part 1

Current cleanup mechanism is awful. It's hardcoded, without repeat on failures,
contains a lot of mistakes, in some places it is too fast (in case of deletion of VMs)
in other to slow (like deletion of users). As well there is mix of cleanup mechanism
and resource cleanup mechanism.
To resolve these all issues this patch introcude a cleanup engine that resolves all issues
above.
It's resource based, so to add new resouce you should just a make subclass of base.Resource
and probably override some of methods like (list, delete, is_deleted) and that's all.
All complexity of managing:
0) waiting until async deletion is finished
1) repeat on failure logic
2) greaceful failure handling
3) parallelization
4) plugin support
Is hidden deep inside cleanup engine
+ bonus we are able to specify now single resource (without clenaping whole service)

PART 1:
-------
* Add new generic cleanup engine
* Fix bug in broker (queue can be empty because of multithreading access)
* Add retry method in rally utils, allow as to repeat few times method on failures

bp benchmark-context-cleanup-refactor

Change-Id: I9f6fb0642b73b7b4d3f6f14de4ef6943a4fb7320

commit_message:
Reduce dnsmasq verbosity and fix logrotate

dnsmasq dhcp logging is extremely verbose and can quickly
fill up logs for dnsmasq. It is not needed in most cases,
so it is now disabled.

Logrotate contained paths relative to rsyslog container,
but logrotate is actually run on Fuel Master host itself.
The paths were updated to be compatible for running
logrotate in a container or on the host.

Closes-Bug: #1382658
blueprint 100-nodes-support

Change-Id: I4290da4c8e3e5585396d105ce8e1f0cfceed61b3

commit_message:
Create DHCP port for IPv6 subnet

There is a bug in dhcp agent code that when first port is created
in an IPv6 subnet, DHCP port is not automatically created.

This fix resolves this problem by removing the IP version check
in configure_dhcp_for_network method.

Change-Id: If3f405d367a7099d9f33d72d11ffcb7a393abe23
Closes-Bug: #1367500

DesignateObjects. Future commits will enhance this to support nested

subject: Fix wrong Default val in AWS_CloudWatch_Alarm.yaml
revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2014-11-13 15:30:48.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/resources/cloud_watch.py', 'etc/heat/templates/AWS_CloudWatch_Alarm.yaml'], 'message': "Fix wrong Default val in AWS_CloudWatch_Alarm.yaml

When Default values equals '', function 'Ref'
gives incorrect result [u''] instead of [].
So this patch fixes this situation and now
'Ref' result is []. Besides that, patch adds
Default value to Dimensions, because it optional
property.

Closes-bug: #1386824
Omission in cloud_watch's properties schema:
there is no 'required' flag in properties, so validation
of CW Alarm resource is incorrect. Following the [1],
this patch add 'required' flag to each param, which is
required.

[1] http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-properties-cw-alarm.html

Change-Id: I003e2e2ec3d497c93108a3dfc275c1589df5873a
Closes-bug: #1386824
"}]
commit_message:
Fix wrong Default val in AWS_CloudWatch_Alarm.yaml

When Default values equals '', function 'Ref'
gives incorrect result [u''] instead of [].
So this patch fixes this situation and now
'Ref' result is []. Besides that, patch adds
Default value to Dimensions, because it optional
property.

Closes-bug: #1386824
Omission in cloud_watch's properties schema:
there is no 'required' flag in properties, so validation
of CW Alarm resource is incorrect. Following the [1],
this patch add 'required' flag to each param, which is
required.

[1] http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-properties-cw-alarm.html

Change-Id: I003e2e2ec3d497c93108a3dfc275c1589df5873a
Closes-bug: #1386824

imported when using the 'from .. import ..' syntax, and the hacking
requirement that it should still be a single module import in either
form.

Add example of multiple imports using the syntax:

 from pkg import module1
 from pkg import module2

To distinguish that the similar pep8 guideline is not acceptable:

 from pkg import module1, module2

Change-Id: I2a0b70ae55a16f4a1fe86e051e408fb3bb8238cd
"}]
commit_message:
Include example of multiple imports using from syntax

This highlights the difference between the pep8 guideline which also
states one module import per line, but allows for multiple modules to be
imported when using the 'from .. import ..' syntax, and the hacking
requirement that it should still be a single module import in either
form.

Add example of multiple imports using the syntax:

 from pkg import module1
 from pkg import module2

To distinguish that the similar pep8 guideline is not acceptable:

 from pkg import module1, module2

Change-Id: I2a0b70ae55a16f4a1fe86e051e408fb3bb8238cd

commit_message:
Increase the readability of the configuration file

* document undocumented parameters
* group similiar parameters
* rename parameter 'stack_pass' to 'stack_password'
* use 'secretsecret' as default value for secrets ('secretsecret' is
  used in the OpenStack manuals as default value)
* add missing dots at the end of sentences
* use 79 chars per line

Change-Id: Ibc667c2375fe39443574e2c424033dd13479cba9

commit_message:
Raise HTTPNotFound in V2 console extension

In case requested instance is not found, console extension does not catch
InstanceNotFound, which results to internal server error (500).

This patch handle InstanceNotFound exception and raise HTTPNotFound
like V3 console plugin.

Change-Id: Ia982049451f2c529f123da714e994476d4610491

commit_message:
Add heat auth_encryption_key handling

via osnailyfacter and it should be used for heat-engine
instances in cloud.
* Disabled start-up and run via pacemaker in case
of HA mode for heat-engine.

commit_message:
Log helpful messages when keystone connection is misconfigured

Add new useHttps configuration to control whether to use https
when talking to keystone. Old way was based on port which doesn't
seem to give enough control

Add AdminAuthException to distinguish between failure to authenticate
the Admin User vs AuthException for authenticating the user token

Build request to authenticate admin user and password using json
instead of StringBuilder so it handles special characters correctly

Fix problem where it was not correctly parsing the token expiration
date so it always got a new one

Log auth failures for user tokens as Info, not Error

Change-Id: I8e97b505577783b6cb7ccdc018b59724408d9f6a

subject: Log helpful messages when keystone connection is misconfigured
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-12 23:15:18.000000000', 'files': ['src/main/java/monasca/api/MonApiApplication.java', 'src/main/resources/mon-api-config.yml', 'src/test/resources/monasca-api-config.yml', 'src/main/java/monasca/api/infrastructure/middleware/MiddlewareConfiguration.java', 'src/main/java/monasca/api/infrastructure/servlet/PreAuthenticationFilter.java'], 'message': "Log helpful messages when keystone connection is misconfigured

Add new useHttps configuration to control whether to use https
when talking to keystone. Old way was based on port which doesn't
seem to give enough control

Return 500 to client instead of 401 if the keystone authentication
is misconfigured.

Add more logging to help user determine what is wrong if the keystone
authentication is misconfigured

Check keystone authentication configuration on startup and exit if it
is set properly

Remove serviceIds and endpointIds from configuration because those
aren't used the keystone v3 and that is all the API will support

Change-Id: I988878f69e06f47bb87f6f2663e498e019810c4c
"}]
commit_message:
Log helpful messages when keystone connection is misconfigured

Add new useHttps configuration to control whether to use https
when talking to keystone. Old way was based on port which doesn't
seem to give enough control

Return 500 to client instead of 401 if the keystone authentication
is misconfigured.

Add more logging to help user determine what is wrong if the keystone
authentication is misconfigured

Check keystone authentication configuration on startup and exit if it
is set properly

Remove serviceIds and endpointIds from configuration because those
aren't used the keystone v3 and that is all the API will support

Change-Id: I988878f69e06f47bb87f6f2663e498e019810c4c

commit_message:
Remove support of '?' operator in expressions and improve performance

This commit removes support of '?' operator (we don't
needed anymore since we fixed the issue with evaluation flow) and
adds expression caching feature and some performance improvements
(JS version). Difference in performance is about ~10 times

Change-Id: I3e3e590d71d8d09800b77c74e8ec4ff17c5d1fab

commit_message:
Squashed two patches that simultaneously block the gate

===

Redis: for non-strict Redis class, expired ttl is None, not -1

Python bindings for Redis return None if ttl is expired instead of -1
when Redis class is used (instead of StrictRedis) which is the default
for oslo-incubator. Fixed unit test to pass the check.

The patch does not belong to master where old RPC layer was removed
since Kilo. Neither it belongs to oslo.messaging since the test was not
copied there.

Closes-Bug: #1259532
Change-Id: Id54e78ca56bb5a5bf1cdad31bc5965ff02c0d9b4

===

Fix build break - switch from str to hash for lookup

Closes-Bug: #1372177
Change-Id: I1a1f70bb204d3f43bdacd4ded53225f8416f1639
(cherry picked from commit 6b65a41dd2653aa9e2558c510fa9d3ca3538a908)
(cherry picked from commit 8957723112cc533f302935dd982ec8dc2b942881)

commit_message:
remove the dsvm-cells job from libraries

Libraries no longer test in a way that these jobs provide any
meaningful results. We should remove them from all the libraries. If
there are specific pieces of function that need testing in these
libraries, we should get them back into the libraries themselves.

This should also remove the coupling that oslo was still seeing with
the rest of the integrated gate.

Change-Id: I889630201e238a300fb16a39f8e43f5d6f3f635e

Disable the waiting for user input if the last boot failed

Add the option GRUB_RECORDFAIL_TIMEOUT to grub and
set it to the same value as the GRUB_TIMEOUT

commit_message:
Fail Fuel Master deployment if puppet or check fails

Puppet apply for Fuel Master deployment runs with
--detailed-exitcodes in order to capture any failures
and fails if any resource fails to apply, including
docker containers.
Cleaned up some obsolete lines about hiera and astute.yaml.

Fixed automated environment deployment scripts to detect
failed deployments and fail as well.

Change-Id: I29238a27f1335d63a6c82274a6dab9b25e1ecf0a
Related-Bug: #1390129

revisions:
[{'number': 56, 'created': '2014-11-13 09:40:08.000000000', 'files': ['rally/exceptions.py', 'rally-scenarios/rally.yaml', 'tests/unit/benchmark/test_utils.py', 'rally/benchmark/utils.py', 'tests/unit/benchmark/context/test_users.py', 'rally/benchmark/context/users.py'], 'message': 'Refactor UserGenerator

1. In the current implementation, it is possible for the UserGenerator to
   create a tenant in _create_tenant_users() and then fail at user creation,
   without returning the created tenant data. As a result, created tenants don't
   get deleted during cleanup.

   Here we refactor the tenants / users creation code by splitting it to two
   different methods, both launched via the Broker pattern.

   We remove the run_concurrent() method that is no longer used.

2. To fix a security issue, we change the password used for temporary users from
   "password" to a randomly generated uuid.

3. We rename the "concurrent" config option in the user context to
   "resource_management_workers".

Change-Id: I0b7f6b5677bb564c044c93aa1a9aeafc3b9f53cc
Closes-Bug: #1347215
Closes-Bug: #1365758
'}]
commit_message:
Refactor UserGenerator

1. In the current implementation, it is possible for the UserGenerator to
   create a tenant in _create_tenant_users() and then fail at user creation,
   without returning the created tenant data. As a result, created tenants don't
   get deleted during cleanup.

   Here we refactor the tenants / users creation code by splitting it to two
   different methods, both launched via the Broker pattern.

   We remove the run_concurrent() method that is no longer used.

2. To fix a security issue, we change the password used for temporary users from
   "password" to a randomly generated uuid.

3. We rename the "concurrent" config option in the user context to
   "resource_management_workers".

Change-Id: I0b7f6b5677bb564c044c93aa1a9aeafc3b9f53cc
Closes-Bug: #1347215
Closes-Bug: #1365758

commit_message:
Composite Authorization and Service Accounts

This proposal originated in the desire to provide a more secure and
convenient way of storing service-specific data (such as Glance
images) in end-user Swift accounts. When discussing this with the
Keystone team, the concept of composite authorization was invented.

Following review at the Swift design summit in Paris, the proposal has
evolved as described here. Feedback from Glance and Cinder developers
has been incorporated into the proposal.

Change-Id: I962b94a253c717b7938953343232fb8837b05b55

commit_message:
Implement Service Validation

Service Validations aims to be used in all OpenStack modules to validate
that services are actually running.

Example in nova::api where we could validate the Nova API is really
working. If it's the case, a Puppet Anchor will be created. This Anchor
could be consummed by external tools to validate a deployment workflow
and improve the orchestration during an OpenStack deployment.

Change-Id: Ia74677b1402c8f872183f873cf9cb73702253874

commit_message:
Disable multi floating ranges when using Neutron

Currently fuel-library doesn't seem to support multiple
floating ranges when using Neutron. Neutron it self does
support multiple floating ranges when using the Python api
although the CLI has no support for this.

This patch will first disable it in the UI as a first step
and the actual support for multiple floating ip ranges with Neutron
in fuel will be added later. We should re-enable the functionality
in UI as soon as we have support in Fuel.

Hacky way - needs change after advanced networking implementation

Related-bug: #1371363

Change-Id: I7917f5b8419b4f36e80a9d1a59291d67c832a4bd

commit_message:
Correct informing about glance problem

Instead of always inform about glance image
problem in every fail deployment now we report
following such rules:

- report about last node only if controller do not present in task.
  This change prevent to unexpecting error report about compute node
  generally.
- report about controller only if controller do not mark as error
  before. This change prevent error about expecting glance problem
  because deployment on contoller already failed.

Change-Id: I5079bcc11b70d889e432fab57ece81ff956b7115
Closes-Bug: #1389651
Closes-Bug: #1389640

[{'number': 11, 'created': '2014-11-12 22:29:51.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/drivers/modules/agent.py', 'ironic/api/controllers/v1/driver.py', 'ironic/drivers/base.py', 'ironic/drivers/fake.py', 'ironic/tests/api/v1/test_nodes.py', 'ironic/tests/conductor/test_rpcapi.py', 'ironic/conductor/rpcapi.py', 'ironic/tests/conductor/test_manager.py', 'ironic/conductor/manager.py', 'ironic/drivers/modules/fake.py', 'ironic/api/controllers/v1/node.py', 'ironic/tests/api/v1/test_drivers.py'], 'message': 'Add sync and async support for passthru methods

This patch extend the @passthru and @driver_passthru decorators to
add support to vendor to determine whether their methods should run
synchronously or asynchronously.

A new flag "async" was added to the decorators, if True (the default)
run the method asynchronously if False synchronously.

The RPC methods vendor_passthru() and driver_vendor_passthru() return
values were updated to also return the mode that the vendor method was
invoked. This is needed because the API should return a different HTTP
code depending on the mode, which is 202 (Accepted) for async and 200
(OK) for sync.

Before the driver_vendor_passthru() was always synchronously and the
vendor_passthru() asynchronously, this patch makes things more consistent
by supporting both modes on both endpoints.

Partial-Bug: #1382457
Implements: blueprint extended-vendor-passthru
Change-Id: I6e7f6c61e9933cba7411d4e9acca9dd8720e9bfe
'}]
commit_message:
Add sync and async support for passthru methods

This patch extend the @passthru and @driver_passthru decorators to
add support to vendor to determine whether their methods should run
synchronously or asynchronously.

A new flag "async" was added to the decorators, if True (the default)
run the method asynchronously if False synchronously.

The RPC methods vendor_passthru() and driver_vendor_passthru() return
values were updated to also return the mode that the vendor method was
invoked. This is needed because the API should return a different HTTP
code depending on the mode, which is 202 (Accepted) for async and 200
(OK) for sync.

Before the driver_vendor_passthru() was always synchronously and the
vendor_passthru() asynchronously, this patch makes things more consistent
by supporting both modes on both endpoints.

Partial-Bug: #1382457
Implements: blueprint extended-vendor-passthru
Change-Id: I6e7f6c61e9933cba7411d4e9acca9dd8720e9bfe

commit_message:
Support installing packages by default

Adds new disk-image-create --install-type option which
can be used to enable alternate install types. The
default install type is 'source'.

The motivation is to eliminate elements like
enable-package-installs which require coupling and also
don't work with elements in multiple element repositories.

This patch does not prevent you from using the previous
DIB_INSTALLTYPE_ variables to customize the install type,
rather it just changes the default so you don't have to
set it so often when using things like packages.

Change-Id: Icee98440fc2251728f2dca30e7c4789a0fd89b93

Source lib/nova when upgrading tempest

In lib/nova is set variable NOVA_BIN_DIR which is later used for setting
cli_dir in tempest.conf. Without including lib/nova the variable is

commit_message:
Set iser_ip_address with a storage network address

The iser_ip_address parameter in /etc/cinder/cinder.conf
has a wrong value.

This parameter has to be configured with the storage
endpoint address, since it is no longer inherits the
iscsi_ip_address by default.

Currently it uses the $my_ip value, which is not capable
to work with RDMA transport (with its default value).

This fix assures that the default iser_ip_address will
use an address with RDMA support, if iSER is chosen as
the iSCSI transport by the user.

Closes-bug: #1387794

Change-Id: If0f67a9dbe80bfc8655dab85a96d3621bdaf38da

commit_message:
Revert the use of lazy loading for mox

    The current fix to make mox not needed in a non dev environment
    includes a lazy-loading pattern in
    horizon/test/jasmine/jasmine.py. This is undesirable because
    we'd like to keep the imports at the top of the file.

Change-Id: I3db7a1986f7236ba0939281e35316742dc2b7ed4

Co-Authored-By: florent <florent.flament-ext@cloudwatt.com>

The 'volumes_drivers' parameter does the same job as the
'vif_driver' parameter, but for volumes instead of vifs.

The API for the LibvirtBaseVolumeDriver class is not

is to instead work in-tree to nova on a branch. This is

libvirt: deprecated volume_drivers config parameter

In Icehouse the 'vif_driver' parameter was deprecated

  commit 9f6070e194504cc2ca2b7f2a2aabbf91c6b81897
  Author: Lars Kellogg-Stedman <lars@redhat.com>
  Date:   Fri Apr 4 14:58:12 2014 -0400

    mark vif_driver as deprecated and log warning

and then in Juno removed

  commit 7561c8ded211d53e8745d1420a73b82bd0fc35cf
  Author: Daniel P. Berrange <berrange@redhat.com>
  Date:   Thu Jul 24 11:53:47 2014 +0100

    libvirt: remove 'vif_driver' config parameter

The 'volumes_drivers' parameter does the same job as the
'vif_driver' parameter, but for volumes instead of vifs.
The reasons for deprecating it, in preparation for its
removal in Lxxxx are thus the same.

The API for the LibvirtBaseVolumeDriver class is not
considered to be a public extension point. As such it
is not required or expected to remain compatible across
releases.

The main reason for its existance is for people who are
developing new cinder drivers, to be able to write out
of tree nova volume drivers. The recommended practice
is to instead work in-tree to nova on a branch. This is
an approach that would be required in order to submit
the work for review and eventual merge in any case.

DocImpact: libvirt.volume_drivers config param for
           nova.conf is deprecated, to be removed in

commit_message:
Fixed typo in doc/source

There was a typo in the Authentication section of the usage.rst
file.

This has been fixed, along with some lining up of comments in the

commit_message:
Assign IPs from networks in each node's group

Previously nodes were assigned incorrect IPs if nodes from
more than one node group were being assigned IPs. All nodes would
be assigned IPs from the last network group processed irrespective
of the node's actual group.

Change-Id: I3d170d23bf3402d88161adb264240b85ebc7bdd4
Closes-bug: #1389160

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2014-11-11 02:35:05.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/notifiers/nova.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/notifiers/test_notifiers_nova.py'], 'message': 'fix event_send for re-assign floating ip

Neutron can associate a floating ip to a new port
without disassociate from original instance port.
This situation will send network changed event only
for new instance port, and that event object contains
the new instance's id.

In this case nova will update new instance's info
but not original one's in nova's database table
instance_info_caches. For nova can get new instance's
id from the above event. So in table instance_info_caches,
both original instance and new instance will have the
same floating ip in their records. And this make it
possible that, in most situation, after your re-assign
floating ip, run "nova list" will return incorrect info,
multiple instances have a same floating ip, and this may
confuse users.

Nova will sync data in table instance_info_caches, but it
may take dozens of seconds.
The new added code will send network changed event for the
original instance, and this will make nova update instance_
_info_caches table in a few seconds.

Change-Id: If3ee11535f649fc51bf1a52806008c1c5c0e73b6
Closes-Bug: 1381886
'}]
commit_message:
fix event_send for re-assign floating ip

Neutron can associate a floating ip to a new port
without disassociate from original instance port.
This situation will send network changed event only
for new instance port, and that event object contains
the new instance's id.

In this case nova will update new instance's info
but not original one's in nova's database table
instance_info_caches. For nova can get new instance's
id from the above event. So in table instance_info_caches,
both original instance and new instance will have the
same floating ip in their records. And this make it
possible that, in most situation, after your re-assign
floating ip, run "nova list" will return incorrect info,
multiple instances have a same floating ip, and this may
confuse users.

Nova will sync data in table instance_info_caches, but it
may take dozens of seconds.
The new added code will send network changed event for the
original instance, and this will make nova update instance_
_info_caches table in a few seconds.

Change-Id: If3ee11535f649fc51bf1a52806008c1c5c0e73b6

commit_message:
Add validation constraints on config inputs

This change adds a new property to the StructuredDeployment class to
enable a check on the config inputs. When this property is set to
'STRICT' we compare the inputs to the supplied input_values property and
we raise an exception if the input_values result in any inputs not being
assigned a value.
By default this is disabled.
I did a small refactor of the code adding a couple of extra methods.
Closes-bug: 1334283

Change-Id: If132163bcaf4eee61a9499808ab264e7b7f80cb2

commit_message:
Fix share manager to save data after driver error

While creating share servers and shares, exceptions can be raised.
At the moment when error occurs some information about
server/share can already exist. This information should be returned
to the manager and stored in database. The best way to send this
information is using exception which is thrown.
Add field detail_data to these exceptions.
Also make manager to save data from new field to the database
when drivers throw exceptions.

Change-Id: I41397c881d0efd28a02c358b64229b5dc60785b3
Partially-implemented: blueprint enhance-share-manager

commit_message:
Make swift post output an error message when failing

swiftclient.shell.st_post was ignoring the result dict
returned from SwiftService.post and therefore giving no
indication when posts failed e.g. due to invalid auth
credentials.

This patch ensures that SwiftService always returns a
result_dict from post() and then checks the result dict.
On failure the shell now outputs the ClientException
message and exits with error code 1.

Also adds unit tests and cleans up some unnecessary mocked
return values in existing tests.

Closes-Bug: 1383243

Change-Id: I111150eb3d026c8d01c2cac13d3613ca7304e5b9

commit_message:
Fix KeyError raised from client Connection

Some client.Connection methods will raise a KeyError
if a response_dict argument is passed and an error
occurs during authentication or making the request.

The fix is straightforward: add a test for existence
of a response_dict before attempting to get it from
kwargs.

The bulk of this patch is adding unit tests for the
response_dict feature.

Closes-Bug: 1381304

Change-Id: Ic7e1b3dfae33909533931c52ac97355867a08a07

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-11-12 17:51:32.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/l3_agent.py', 'neutron/tests/unit/test_l3_agent.py'], 'message': "Fix for FIPs duplicated across hosts for DVR

For DVR, FIPs should be hosted on the single node
which hosts the VM assigned with the fixed_ip of the FIP.
The l3_agent should only take action on the correct FIP per
host by filtering the FIPs based on the 'host' value
of the FIP.

A recent refactor on the l3_agent moved the host filtering logic
from process_router_floating_ip_addresses() to
_get_external_device_interface_name(). The local floating_ips var
was not altered as it was before the refactor.

This resulted in network disruption across multiple hosts
since more than one namespace contained the FIP.  This problem
would only be seen in a mutli-host environment where the same
router hosting FIPs was present on more than one node.

The fix is to return the host filtering logic by adding a
call to get_floating_ips().  In addition, the unit test
test_process_router_dist_floating_ip_add() was modified to
pass two FIPs instead of one.  One FIP matches the host
of the agent, one does not.  Only one should be processed,
not two.

Change-Id: I67b19f6228af392519fff89b13283b43921552bf
Closes-bug: #1389880
"}]
commit_message:
Fix for FIPs duplicated across hosts for DVR

For DVR, FIPs should be hosted on the single node
which hosts the VM assigned with the fixed_ip of the FIP.
The l3_agent should only take action on the correct FIP per
host by filtering the FIPs based on the 'host' value
of the FIP.

A recent refactor on the l3_agent moved the host filtering logic
from process_router_floating_ip_addresses() to
_get_external_device_interface_name(). The local floating_ips var
was not altered as it was before the refactor.

This resulted in network disruption across multiple hosts
since more than one namespace contained the FIP.  This problem
would only be seen in a mutli-host environment where the same
router hosting FIPs was present on more than one node.

The fix is to return the host filtering logic by adding a
call to get_floating_ips().  In addition, the unit test
test_process_router_dist_floating_ip_add() was modified to
pass two FIPs instead of one.  One FIP matches the host
of the agent, one does not.  Only one should be processed,
not two.

Change-Id: I67b19f6228af392519fff89b13283b43921552bf
Closes-bug: #1389880

commit_message:
Software config notify deployment progress

Currently when a deployment resource remains IN_PROGRESS the only option is to
ssh into a server to diagnose the issue. This proposes that the
server signal to heat when any deployment activity starts.

Specifies: bp software-config-progress
Change-Id: Iaf611186f1ca286116c29bf7c94578254a70d312

commit_message:
user is no longer required for init-keystone

Since init-keystone can now be told whether or not to perform PKI
setup, user can be demoted from a required by default parameter to
an optional parameter, only required when performing PKI setup.

commit_message:
Change ComputeHost table to filter on host field

ComputeHost table was trying to filter on a field that didn't exist
leading to a template rendering error when the filter was applied, so
this patch changes from 'service.type' to 'service.host' as the filtered
field.

Change-Id: I66a47a98f4005689b7be73bec46fa3ea4b9472af
Closes-Bug: 1390089

commit_message:
suds-jurko - Alternative to suds library for py 3.x support

oslo.vmware would like to support 3.x but suds library is not
maintained and won't work under python 3. suds-jurko is the
most active fork of suds. Moving over projects will be a
step-by-step effort starting with oslo.vmware and then followed
by Nova and Cinder, once the CI jobs stabilize (both our CI and
MineSweeper), we should remove suds entirely from requirements.

We discussed this at the Design summit session for python3 and
there was consensus on this approach.

Change-Id: If91a87ede96a82a2a0d181ee0d4fdc102dc0299d

[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-10-28 07:02:07.000000000', 'files': ['glance/cmd/registry.py'], 'message': "Use unicode for error message

Prior to this change, glance-reg would encounter an error, then
encounter an error reporting the first error. Glance-reg would end up
dead with the only error message printed being about the fact that the
first error message wasn't unicode.

After this change, glance-reg still dies just as readily - but on the
way down, it manages to emit the original error message. In my case,
this means that I now know that the original fault is that it can't bind
to 0.0.0.0:9191

Change-Id: I0e90b538996f87fe100c973fdf1fb61791e4e660
closes-bug: 1383255
"}]
commit_message:
Use unicode for error message

Prior to this change, glance-reg would encounter an error, then
encounter an error reporting the first error. Glance-reg would end up
dead with the only error message printed being about the fact that the
first error message wasn't unicode.

After this change, glance-reg still dies just as readily - but on the
way down, it manages to emit the original error message. In my case,
this means that I now know that the original fault is that it can't bind
to 0.0.0.0:9191

Change-Id: I0e90b538996f87fe100c973fdf1fb61791e4e660
closes-bug: 1383255

commit_message:
Add selection of Django session engine to this module

This allows Django to be set to use something other than
the default session engine through Puppet. By default,
it will have no impact on existing configurations.

We've added this because our security constraints make signed cookies
as a session store for Horizon undesirable. The reasons for this are:

  * Sessions become vulnerable to replay attacks,
    a clean log-out is difficult to achieve.
  * Serializing sessions in cookies may allow an attacker
    to escalate read-only access to server configuration
    into code execution via deserialization of attacker-generated
    content.

Conflicts:
  spec/classes/horizon_init_spec.rb
  templates/local_settings.py.erb

Change-Id: Iaf80bdc1bb9ce55ff46b2dcfac73daad90fd0d37
(cherry picked from commit 325db8a86c56b5d56d5b3e4aea20013318dd1d94)

commit_message:
Reverse fix for 1323866 as it regressed trove CLI

Trove CLI appears to be broken (fresh checkout, devstack as well as
openstack gate). All commands fail with

ERROR: __init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'http_log_debug'

Correcting the obvious place where this appears to be an issue is
causing additional failures and as it is time-critical to get this
back up and running, I'm proposing a reversal of the change from
3c47a1855b7ee1345dadfb00ae90a6279b7c424e while that change is
completely reworked.

I will ping trove core for an approval on this and if I don't get an

commit_message:
Revert "remove heat test_updates tests"

This reverts commit 0ca4933e9cb5ffc0536d087a30c3c911f21320b6
and also skips test_stack_update_add_remove.

The heat change which caused the failure burst has been reverted
in change Ieea739bc45dcc365ccb6f09d0e848e310d327134 which leaves
the original very-rarely failure on postgres jobs which we are
continuing to diagnose.

Also as pointed out in the ensuing discussion, this test is valid,
has an appropriate design, and has raised a real (rare) race.

I propose that this bug be reproduced in an in-tree functional test
and that it should be possible to run this test many times to trigger
the race.

Related-Bug: #1370865
Change-Id: If92386fa1ce6be5513c852fc599e7d457c57625b

commit_message:
Improve testing of domain federation tokens for inherited roles.

Currently domain-scoped federation-generated tokens incorrectly
include group roles that are inherited projects within that domain.
This error is also exposed via the /auth/domains and
/OS-FEDERATION/domains API calls.

This patch enhances our testing to demonstrate the error - a follow-on
patch will fix it.

Partially implements: bug 1385533
Partially implements: bug 1385643

Change-Id: I54d1d1a38cb63208c626efa5e4ca4a69e1b234a1

commit_message:
Hyper-V: Skip logging out in-use targets

As most of the Cinder volume drivers that use iSCSI export one LUN
per iSCSI target, the Hyper-V driver was logging out the according
target each time a volume was disconnected.

This causes issues with some volume drivers that use multiple LUNs
per iSCSI target and may disconnect in-use targets.

This patch fixes the issue by checking if there are other LUNs
being used, disconnecting the iSCSI targets otherwise.

Change-Id: Ida08e7129a7b7940ddea488488cccc7571a43b76
Closes-Bug: #1372815

commit_message:
Basic multitenancy for policies

This change adds the ability to create/delete new policies
via the API.  This enables the most basic form of multitenancy.
All of the policies share a single copy of the datasource data.

This change also resurrects a number of tests that had
been mothballed because of a small shift in architecture.

Supporting multi-tenancy properly requires implementing policies so
that the datasource data is stored separately from the
policy rules, so that all policies can share the same datasource
data. This separation makes it simple to close out the bug
where the Service policy appears empty.

Closes-bug: 1352541
Change-Id: I9cd179fa48b9018306c4fc518a04ffac7a43d0f4

commit_message:
Fix the help comment about metadata

If passing metadata with "--meta" option, the metadata is stored into
meta_data.json file on the metadata server like:

 $ curl http://169.254.169.254/openstack/latest/meta_data.json
 {
     "hostname": "vm01.novalocal",
     "meta": {"key01": "value01", "key02": "value02"},
     "name": "vm01",
     [..]
 }

This patch fixes the help comment.

Change-Id: I7359d4c2b0aec6d5d07be7938d0000ca23c93ff0

commit_message:
Implement functionality for functional tests using tempest-lib

Add generic functionality for functional tests using tempest-lib and
create related tox jobs.

Run of functional tests requires:

1) Access to deployed OpenStack with running, at least, Keystone and Manila
services.

2) Defined config options to be able to execute requests to Manila,
Manilaclient should know auth related information like username, password,
tenant_name, etc...

3) Run of functional tests searches for following optional env vars to be set:
'OS_MANILACLIENT_CONFIG_FILE' - name of conf file, default 'manilaclient.conf'
'OS_MANILACLIENT_CONFIG_DIR' - path to conf dir,
  default '%project_dir%/etc/manilaclient'
'OS_MANILA_EXEC_DIR' - path to dir with manilaclient executable,
  default '%project_dir%/.tox/functional/bin'

4) Config sample can be generated by following new tox job:
$ tox -egenconfig
it will create sample in
"%project_dir%/etc/manilaclient/manilaclient.conf.sample"
then just rename it removing ".sample" part and set option values.

To run functional tests use following new tox job:
$ tox -efunctional

To run only some specific tests use following:
$ tox -efunctional manilaclient.tests.functional.foo.bar

Partially implements blueprint functional-tests

Change-Id: I95a4e441d2143e51c54ec4fb47a069a91ed77dd7

commit_message:
Add new filter for Nova Scheduler

We need to use filter ServerGroupAffinityFilter
in nova.conf to fix issues with fails of several
Tempest tests. We want to deploy OpenStack cloud
which will pass all Tempest tests and in this case
we need to add this filter to Nova config file.

Change-Id: I3e74078d69917c295ca27a054610f78c186292bb
Closes-Bug: #1389701

commit_message:
Add new filter for Nova Scheduler

We need to use filter ServerGroupAffinityFilter
in nova.conf to fix issues with fails of several
Tempest tests. We want to deploy OpenStack cloud
which will pass all Tempest tests and in this case
we need to add this filter to Nova config file.

Change-Id: I3e74078d69917c295ca27a054610f78c186292bb
Closes-Bug: #1389701

commit_message:
Use RPC directly for software config operations

This change replaces heatclient REST calls with RPC calls when
creating, fetching or deleting software configs.

All resources can now request and RPC client with self.rpc_client()
which will create and memoize an EngineClient instance.

Change-Id: Id23749e672fd4154e3d9986e22b46fc038579d8e
Partial-blueprint: software-config-trigger

Add REMOTE_USER mapping info in federation docs.

Reflect changes proposed in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/133037/ .
With the patch it is no longer compulsory to specify the rule for
``user_name`` mapping. If such rule is missing, a ``REMOTE_USER`` is
attempted.

commit_message:
add tooltip to cells if 'truncate' variable is set

If a Column has the 'truncate' variable defined, we should
have a tooltip to show the full text if user hovers over
a cell. For example, Project > Volumes Description column is
truncated at 40 chars. 'Truncate' column attribute should be
used on Strings, not Integers, fixed test case.

Change-Id: I960744f73b84e54d196e264039ebba9614db372b
Closes-Bug: #1369944

commit_message:
Add filtering to  share-network-list command

Add filtering share networks command by model's keys:
- name,
- project-id (admin context)
- neutron-net,
- neutron-subnet,
- network-type,
- segmentation-id,
- cidr,
- ip-version,
by associated security service, by creation date.

Add '--offset' and '--limit' options to specify start point
of share networks listing and number of share networks to show.

Remove filtering by status as share_network model doesn't have
such attribute.

Implements bp improve-share-network-list-filtering

Change-Id: Ia9c1e91da480d43cbaf77795691c3c13d5fec94c

commit_message:
Fix bug in swift-ring-builder list_parts

The number of shown replicas in the partition list might differ from the
actual number of replicas (as shown in the bugreport).

This codes simply iterates for the builder._replica2part2dev and
remembers the number of replicas for each partition.

The code to find the partitions was moved to swift/common/ring/utils.py
to make it easier to test, and a test to ensure the correct number of
replicas is returned was added.

Closes-Bug: 1370070
Change-Id: Id6a3ed437bb86df2f43f8b0b79aa8ccb50bbe13e

commit_message:
Includes a validation to disable creating initial networks for Neutron

Neutron external and internal networks are created by default
This commit let developers by configuration to decide if those
networks needs to be created. This is needed to test Neutron DVR
in a distributed Multi-node environment

Change-Id: I17d891d072f189925676b4557094cde1c7a71579
Closes-Bug: 1389288

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-10 08:17:33.000000000', 'files': ['functions-common'], 'message': 'Drop PIP_USE_MIRRORS environment variable

The PIP_USE_MIRRORS does not do anything else than adding
 the --use-mirrors option to the pip command line.

The --use-mirrors is deprecated since pip-1.5,
and does not do anything else than printing a warning message.

For using alternate pypi index url this option is not required and

commit_message:
Drop PIP_USE_MIRRORS environment variable

The PIP_USE_MIRRORS does not do anything else than adding
 the --use-mirrors option to the pip command line.

The --use-mirrors is deprecated since pip-1.5,
and does not do anything else than printing a warning message.

For using alternate pypi index url this option is not required and
not sufficient. The current way for using alternate mirrors
is to defining them in the .pip/pip.conf either manually (before
devstack), or by using the PYPI_ALTERNATIVE_URL and PYPI_OVERRIDE
environment variables.

Change-Id: Ia33e783360e5661c2ef03b77e9f7af32b2633f2f

commit_message:
Add note in template about asking for preliminary feedback

Allow people to post the first half of a spec to get feedback on the
problem statement and outline of the solution. If we don't think the
problem should be fixed in nova, then no point in making the author fill
out all the details about the fix.

commit_message:
Enable services required by vpn drivers

According different vpn drivers, we should make sure different
prerequisite services are enabled, for example, neutron-vpn-agent is
based on ipsec now, so we should enable ipsec service in our recipe.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1390378

Change-Id: I6f55cc992badc97426578a232f9a5c0eda6e81bb

commit_message:
Added chef-vault as option to store secrets

*Added gem chef-vault to gemfile
*Added method to decrypt chef-vault items
*Added case for ['openstack']['databag_type'] = 'vault'
*Added version for ['openstack']['vault_gem_version'] = '~> 2.3'
*Moved ::Chef.log.warn for developer_mode from method 'secret' to private method
'dev_secret' to refactore and shrink the method 'secret'
*Added link to opscode chef-vault documentation

Change-Id: Icda0e288bbb920498aba856fefaf04c0f1852787

commit_message:
Fix indent exclusion

The current dib-lint script has an exclusion for indent but it is
erroneously used as a label around the tab indention check.  This
patch renames the tab indention exclusion and adds the indent
exclusion where it belongs.

Change-Id: I701595e7a08f4764a45c6701d67cbb931c3d47f3

commit_message:
Purge use of "PRED and A or B" poor-mans-ternary

Since python2.6, python has a proper ternary construct "A if PRED else
B".  The older idiom "PRED and A or B" has a hidden trap - when A is
itself false, the result is (unexpectedly) B.

This change removes all cases of the older construct found using a
trivial git grep " and .* or " - except one case in oslo common
code (fixed in oslo upstream).

Change-Id: I24461f4328e188c8983ad574495e11e033ec5ba4

commit_message:
change client libraries to test from pypi instead of git

We are making devstack use client libraries from pypi instead of from
git. Before we do that we need to change the client library job
definitions to support testing themselves against changes in their own
git trees. This is equivalent to what was done with the oslo libraries.

This adds the lib-forward-testing to the client libraries for testing,
and purges the integrated gate jobs from them. It also changes the
stable-compat jobs to be driving by -src-{name} jobs, which will test
a client library with openstack servers from git, all the rest of the
client libraries from pypi, and the {name} library from git. So a
python-novaclient change will be tested with nova stable/*, released
glance/cinder clients, but the new zuul ref for python-novaclient.

Co-Authored-By: Joshua Hesketh <josh@nitrotech.org>

Needed-By: I26fac0ccf8fd4818e24618d56bf04b32306f88f6

Change-Id: I81b0d228e7769758c61e5b0323ecfce8c8886d39

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-11 09:27:41.000000000', 'files': ['mirror/ubuntu/multistrap.conf', 'mirror/ubuntu/createchroot.mk'], 'message': 'mirror-ubuntu: use the OSCI repo for bootstrapping the chroot

If some of the base packages (like python-minimal) has been rebuilt
we should use them when bootstrapping the temporary chroot. Otherwise
the newly created apt repo will contain either only upstream version of
the package in question, or both the upstream and customized versions.

Assume that the base package X has been customized. The customized version
of X is located on the OSCI mirror. Multistrap does not use that mirror, so
the upstream version of X gets pulled into the apt cache (typically
/var/apt/cache/archives) during bootstrapping of the chroot. Packages
depending on X pull its customized version (since the OSCI repo is added
to the sources.list.d after bootstrapping the chroot). If X is an essential
package (so other packages are not obliged to declare dependence on X)
only the upstream version of X gets into the apt repo being created.

Use the OSCI mirror when bootstrapping the chroot to avoid the problem.

While at it reduce copy-paste noise in createchroot.mk and make it a little
bit less obscure.

Related-bug: #1390416
Related-bug: #1390044
Related-bug: #1383641

Change-Id: Ic418c760a1635d5c72cc108658d412228fb83a62
'}]
commit_message:
mirror-ubuntu: use the OSCI repo for bootstrapping the chroot

If some of the base packages (like python-minimal) has been rebuilt
we should use them when bootstrapping the temporary chroot. Otherwise
the newly created apt repo will contain either only upstream version of
the package in question, or both the upstream and customized versions.

Assume that the base package X has been customized. The customized version
of X is located on the OSCI mirror. Multistrap does not use that mirror, so
the upstream version of X gets pulled into the apt cache (typically
/var/apt/cache/archives) during bootstrapping of the chroot. Packages
depending on X pull its customized version (since the OSCI repo is added
to the sources.list.d after bootstrapping the chroot). If X is an essential
package (so other packages are not obliged to declare dependence on X)
only the upstream version of X gets into the apt repo being created.

Use the OSCI mirror when bootstrapping the chroot to avoid the problem.

While at it reduce copy-paste noise in createchroot.mk and make it a little
bit less obscure.

Related-bug: #1390416
Related-bug: #1390044
Related-bug: #1383641

Change-Id: Ic418c760a1635d5c72cc108658d412228fb83a62

commit_message:
Encapsulate getting image for a deployment.

By encapsulating getting of images we can transparently
download them, or use them from cache, or build them, without
having to reproduce the logic in every script.

Change-Id: Iae40275bf94c644a552ace98805b75a6f2afcce1

commit_message:
Split up extracting Ironic driver_info method

The register_ironic_node method in nodes.py does a couple of things.
It does the extracting Ironic driver_info, and creating Ironic node.
